						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up to the east of the ruined <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in Survey No. 395 to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>10th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated inscription may be assigned to the 10th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Slightly damaged. Registers the gift of an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> namely Immaḍi dēvāgrahāra by Kumāra Kēsiya rāju to certain Bhīmasinga bhaṭṭāra.</p>						

